FRENCH MUSLIM YOUTHS PROTEST POLICE ACTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 French Muslim youths set fire to six cars in the northern town of Amiens 
during a second consecutive night of anti-police protests, officials said 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 A few dozen youths demonstrated in the streets and no injuries were reported, 
officials said. Over the weekend, about 16 police were injured, some by shotgun 
pellets, in a riot by 200 people. 
</P>
