 Chief wide receiver Michael Young, a former Ram, retired because of a back 
injury. Young, 32, from UCLA, played four years with Denver and one with 
Philadelphia. . . . The Dolphins waived running back Mark Higgs. . . . Steeler 
tight end Eric Green (pulled hamstring) and rookie running back Bam Morris 
(leg-muscle contusion) are doubtful for Sunday's game against the Dolphins. . . 
. Chief defensive end Neil Smith, running back Marcus Allen and cornerback Mark 
Collins might miss Sunday's game against the Browns because of injuries. 
