<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; ANOTHER UPSET FOR CALABASAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Shera Wiegler, Deb Pepkowitz and Amanda Cey swept their three singles sets to 
lead Calabasas High to a 10-8 upset over Diamond Bar in a Southern Section 
Division II girls' tennis quarterfinal Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory marked the Coyotes' second consecutive playoff victory over an 
undefeated team. 
</P>
<P>
 Calabasas (15-4) defeated Arcadia (17-1) on Saturday before ousting 
third-seeded Diamond Bar (23-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Nordhoff 10, Rancho Cucamonga 8 -- Stacey Roberts swept all three singles sets 
for the Rangers (13-6) in the Division V quarterfinals at the Ojai Valley 
Racquet Club. 
</P>
<P>
 Dana Hills 11, Camarillo 7 -- Monique Allegre swept her three singles sets, 
but it was not enough in the Division I quarterfinals at Dana Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 Darian Chappell, Camarillo's No. 2 singles player, won two of her three 
matches. But Camarillo (17-3) won only two of nine doubles matches. 
</P>
<P>
 La Reina 16, Connelly 2 -- The fourth-seeded Regents had few problems in a 
Division V quarterfinal match. GIRLS' VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Harvard-Westlake d. Notre Dame Academy, 13-15, 5-15, 15-10, 15-6, 15-12 -- The 
Wolverines (15-4) rallied from the verge of elimination in a Division II 
quarterfinal at Notre Dame Academy. Amanda Selby and Christine Bohle each had 
21 kills for Harvard-Westlake (15-4). 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor d. Agoura, 15-7, 15-3, 15-5 -- The Chargers (15-3) fell to the 
state's top team in a Division I quarterfinal at Newport Harbor (27-1). Misty 
May led Newport Harbor with 16 kills. 
</P>
<P>
 L.A. Baptist d. South Hills, 15-13, 13-15, 15-10, 15-7 -- Darcie Frazier had 
26 kills and 17 digs for the Knights (18-0) in a Division V game. 
</P>
<P>
 Tunde Hrotko added 45 assists. Angela McHenry had 14 kills and nine blocks for 
South Hills (15-7). 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Ynez d. La Reina, 10-15, 15-5, 16-14, 3-15, 15-7 -- Shane Anderson had 
23 kills and 14 blocks in a losing effort for the Regents (19-4) in a Division 
IV quarterfinal at La Reina. 
</P>
<P>
 Nordhoff d. Corona Centennial, 15-5, 15-10, 15-9 -- The second-seeded Rangers 
(16-1) swept a Division IV quarterfinal at Corona Centennial. MEN'S BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Glendale 76, Santa Barbara 68 -- Maurice Sowells scored 27 points, Eric Scott 
and Charlie Garcia each had 14 and Maurice McIntosh had 13 for the Vaqueros in 
a Western State Conference interdivisional game at Glendale. 
</P>
<P>
 Valley 68, East L.A. 49 -- Lamarr Thompson, a freshman from Sylmar High, had 
15 points and 14 rebounds in a nonconference game at Valley (3-0). WOMEN'S 
BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Valley 60, Victor Valley 55 -- Valery Brady scored 13 points and Erika Kusek 
came off the bench to get 10 for Valley (3-0) in a nonconference game. 
</P>
<P>
 Diana Sullivan scored 18 points for Victor Valley (0-2). 
</P>
