 But Mikels said she may attend the two follow-up orientations that are 
scheduled in Northern California next year. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's really helpful, but I've done several of those types of training 
seminars with the League of California Cities," Mikels said. 
</P>
<P>
 The board on Tuesday agreed to cover the $350 registration costs for each to 
attend the seminar series. JEFF McDONALD 
