<TEXT>
<P>
 Two families were left homeless Tuesday afternoon when their adjoining Santa 
Paula apartments were damaged by fire, according to the Ventura County Chapter 
of the Red Cross. 
</P>
<P>
 No one was injured in the blaze at 130 W. Harvard Blvd. 
</P>
