<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: CAMARILLO; CHARITY AUCTION FOCUSES ON FANTASY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By IRA E. STOLL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fantasy is the theme of an auction and dinner scheduled for Camarillo on 
Saturday to benefit Catholic Charities of Ventura County. 
</P>
<P>
 Catholic Charities Director A. Diane Martell said 21 donated "fantasy 
packages" will be auctioned at the event, including a seven-day Mexican Riviera 
cruise for two, a trip to the Grand Canyon and vacations in Ojai and New 
Orleans. 
</P>
<P>
 Also in keeping with the fantasy theme, guests will be able to purchase $25 
"fantasy balloons," with mystery prizes attached worth between $25 and $200, 
Martell said. In addition, a magician is scheduled to perform. 
</P>
<P>
 Martell said the idea is to make fantasies come true, not just for bidders who 
attend the $100-a-person benefit at Spanish Hills Country Club, but for people 
who will be helped with the money raised. 
</P>
<P>
 "The event is to benefit those families in Ventura County for whom three meals 
a day is a fantasy, those children for whom a permanent place to call home is a 
fantasy," Martell said. 
</P>
<P>
 Organizers said they hope the auction will raise $30,000 to help fund Catholic 
Charities' social services, counseling, child care and elder care programs, 
which last year served more than 29,000 people in Ventura County. 
</P>
<P>
 The dinner is scheduled to begin at 6:30 p.m., with the auction to follow. For 
tickets or more information call Catholic Charities at 643-4694. IRA E. STOLL 
</P>
</TEXT>
