EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; FUNDS APPROVED FOR NEW TRAFFIC SIGNALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hoping to improve the flow of traffic on Simi Valley thoroughfares, the City 
Council has agreed to install two new signals and upgrade three others. 
</P>
<P>
 New traffic lights will be installed at Alamo Street and Texas Avenue and at 
Royal Avenue and Vaquero Drive, the council agreed Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition, red left-turn arrows will be removed from the intersections of 
Bonita Drive and Madera Road, Cochran Street and Galena Avenue, and at Cochran 
and Stearns streets. 
</P>
<P>
 Removing the red arrows will allow vehicles more time to turn, traffic 
engineer Bill Golubics said. 
</P>
<P>
 The city will spend $156,000 on the project. SARA CATANIA 
