<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; CITY SUBSIDIZES POLICE CAR PURCHASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Faced with a substantial increase in the cost of police cars, the Simi Valley 
Police Department will receive a subsidy from the city to buy seven new 
cruisers. 
</P>
<P>
 The City Council on Monday agreed to pitch in an additional $23,000 to help 
cover the cost of the Chevrolet Caprices, which have increased in price by 
$5,000 each since last year, according to a staff report. 
</P>
<P>
 Prices have gone up because General Motors stopped subsidizing the sale of 
police cars, the report said. 
</P>
<P>
 The cruisers, which are purchased through the County of Los Angeles 
Cooperative Purchasing Program, now cost about $19,800 each. The department 
replaces police cars at 85,000 miles. SARA CATANIA 
