<HEADLINE>
<P>
LIGHT RAIN TO DIMINISH BY MID-MORNING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A storm front moving in from Central California is expected to bring light to 
moderate rainfall to Orange County this morning, weather forecasters said. 
</P>
<P>
 Rain should begin countywide around dawn but taper off by mid-morning, said 
meteorologists with WeatherData Inc. However, showers may continue through 
mid-afternoon in isolated areas in the county, they said. 
</P>
<P>
 The storm should drop between .10 of an inch and .50 of an inch of rain across 
the county. 
</P>
<P>
 "It doesn't look like that much precipitation," Curtis Brack of WeatherData 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 By tonight, skies should be clear and low temperatures in the 40s, Brack said. 
</P>
