<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE SOCCER ROUNDUP; WIND, CYPRESS ROAR PAST RANCHO SANTIAGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Carlye Wind scored three goals and Kim Wyer added two for Cypress in its 7-0 
shutout of Rancho Santiago on Tuesday in an Orange Empire Conference women's 
soccer game at Cypress. 
</P>
<P>
 The Chargers (15-0-2, 13-0-2), who clinched their third consecutive Orange 
Empire Conference crown last Thursday, had a 5-0 halftime lead and did not 
allow Rancho Santiago any shots on goal. 
</P>
<P>
 In other women's conference soccer: 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine Valley 2, Orange Coast 0 -- Shannon Cunningham scored two second-half 
goals for host Irvine Valley (13-5-1, 10-4-1), which kept its playoff hopes 
alive. Orange Coast is 13-6, 10-5. 
</P>
<P>
 In Orange Empire Conference men's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Coast 2, Irvine Valley 0 -- Athanasios Koubouras and Matt Hicks scored 
goals for host OCC (10-4-4, 6-3-2), which clinched second place. 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago 8, Cypress 2 -- Andy Ostelie scored two goals and Francisco 
Islas scored two goals for host Rancho Santiago (14-2-3, 9-1-1), which led, 
5-0, at halftime. 
</P>
</TEXT>
