ATHLETE OF THE WEEK: BOYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Eric Blair 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Ventura 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Football 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Senior 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: Blair (5 foot 10, 175 pounds) has played sparingly at 
running back this season but as a defensive back has played every down. Coach 
Phil McCune decided Blair was better suited than the team's other backs to play 
offense against Oxnard and was put in the starting backfield. 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: In a game the Cougars needed to win to make the Southern 
Section playoffs, Blair gained 201 yards in 12 carries, including touchdown 
runs of 37 and 66 yards, to help Ventura post a 57-32 victory over Oxnard. He 
also returned an interception 48 yards for another score. Blair had managed 
only 244 yards in 44 carries over the first nine games. "It was phenomenal," 
McCune said. "He played great." 
</P>
