opening two rounds of the 4-A playoffs. She had five aces in second-seeded 
Chatsworth's 15-3, 15-3, 15-3 victory over Narbonne. Against undefeated Van 
Nuys, Hodges had 14 blocks and 12 kills in a 16-14, 15-10, 15-13 victory over 
the seventh-seeded Wolves. "Her blocking was outstanding," Coach Bud Dow said. 
"It was her best game of the year." 
