<P>
COLLEGE SIGNINGS; SAN CLEMENTE'S GARDNER TO PLAY VOLLEYBALL AT USC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gabe Gardner, a two-sport standout at San Clemente, signed a letter of intent 
with USC to play volleyball, San Clemente boys' volleyball Coach Mike Hurlbut 
said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Gardner, a 6-foot-9 outside hitter, was a first-team all-county selection by 
The Times and an All-Southern Section Division I selection last season.He also 
is a goalkeeper for the water polo team. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Eric Ambrozich, a 6-8 center at Saddleback College, has signed a letter of 
intent with Hawaii, Saddleback basketball Coach Bill Brummel said. 
</P>
<P>
 Ambrozich, from Irvine High, earned Orange Empire Conference honorable-mention 
honors after averaging 10.5 points, 6.2 rebounds and a block last season. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Chris Toomey, a right-handed pitcher and outfielder at Dana Hills, has signed 
a letter of intent to play baseball at Arizona State, Dolphin Coach Bob Canary 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Toomey transferred to Dana Hills from University before his junior year. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Lutheran's Michelle Harrison, an All-Olympic League pitcher, has signed 
a letter of intent with Southwest Texas State. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Susie Erickson, a SCATS gymnast who attends Marina, has signed a letter of 
intent with UCLA. 
</P>
