<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: GOLF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Brandon DiTullio of Westlake High signed a letter of intent with UCLA on 
Tuesday.DiTullio qualified for the State Amateur and U.S. Junior Amateur last 
summer. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Michael Haney of Glendale and Dave Olsen of Sherman Oaks fired their second 
consecutive four-under-par 68 to finish tied for third in the Southern 
California Golf Assn. Four-Ball Championship at Oakmont Country Club in 
Glendale. 
</P>
<P>
 Haney and Olsen finished four shots behind Bob Clark of Murrieta and Ed Cuff 
Jr. of Temecula, who birdied three of the last four holes to shoot a 
second-round 67. 
</P>
