<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: IIJIMA, MISSION WIN STATE GOLF TITLES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FERNANDO DOMINGUEZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kumiko Iijima shot a four-over-par 76 and led Mission College to the first 
junior college women's golf state championship Monday at Menefee Lakes Country 
Club in Temecula. 
</P>
<P>
 Iijima won the individual title on the 5,400-yard course. The other team 
members at the championships were Mikel Alpert, Creela Harris, Jill 
Burton-Jones and Layne Burr. Another member, Cathy Gallegos-Kehoe, did not 
play. 
</P>
<P>
 The Free Spirit shot 372 in the four-team, 18-hole event. Desert finished 
second at 398 and Mt. San Antonio third at 417. Rio Hondo was disqualified 
because one of its five players did not complete the course. FERNANDO DOMINGUEZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
