<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF FLETCHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Zack Hernandez, a former All-Southern Section quarterback from L.A. Baptist 
High, will leave Cal Lutheran to play junior college football, Kingsmen Coach 
Joe Harper said. 
</P>
<P>
 Hernandez could not be reached for comment, but Harper said his impression is 
that Hernandez wants to play junior college football as a means to earning a 
Division I scholarship. 
</P>
<P>
 Hernandez redshirted his freshman season at Division III Cal Lutheran this 
year. JEFF FLETCHER 
