<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: FOOTBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DANA HADDAD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sophomore running back Jeff McKinley, Canyon High's leading rusher who has 
been declared academically ineligible, and two other Cowboys will not be in 
uniform for the team's Southern Section Division II playoff opener against 
Peninsula at Torrance High on Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Also missing will be senior tight end Rob Varnon, who quit the team last 
week.Backup quarterback Brian Bialas, who quit the team last season, was voted 
off the squad by his teammates, Mohr said. 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon (3-5-1) will add two players for the game against Peninsula (9-1), the 
No. 1 team from the Bay League. Senior Konstantin Chigrin, a senior defensive 
tackle, will make his first varsity start after securing academic eligibility 
Monday. In addition, running back Monte McKeon will be promoted from the 
sophomore team to replace McKinley. DANA HADDAD 
</P>
