<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION GIRLS' TENNIS PLAYOFFS; NO. 3 CORONA DEL MAR ROLLS INTO 
SEMIFINALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MELANIE NEFF 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Corona del Mar advanced to the semifinals of the Southern Section Division I 
tennis playoffs with a 14-4 victory over Santa Barbara San Marcos Tuesday at 
Corona del Mar. 
</P>
<P>
 The third-seeded Sea Kings were led by their doubles teams, winners of eight 
of nine matches.That helped give Corona del Mar a 5-1 lead after the first 
round. 
</P>
<P>
 In the second round, Corona del Mar put the match out of reach, taking a 9-3 
lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Seniors Ranee Rhodes and Melissa Allinson keyed the victory, sweeping their 
sets, 7-6, 7-6, 6-0. Rhodes and Allinson were down, 1-4, against Apolka 
Patruska and Stacey Holmes in the second set, but the pair won their second 
tie-breaker of the day. 
</P>
<P>
 "We were confident we'd win," Rhodes said. "We just kept playing hard." 
</P>
<P>
 Christie O'Meara and partner Jenny Glasgow easily swept their sets, 6-3, 6-0, 
6-0, and sophomores Marisol Perea and Ashley Harrington won, 6-3, 1-6, 6-0. 
</P>
<P>
 In singles, Corona del Mar (17-4) was unable to get by the Royals' top player, 
Kara Warkentin, who swept, 6-4, 6-2, 6-4. 
</P>
<P>
 In singles, Alissa Scott won, 6-3, 6-0, 4-6. Freshman Nina Vaughan lost her 
first set of the playoffs to Warkentin, 6-4, but rebounded in her final two 
sets, 6-1, 6-3. Junior Megan Wachtler also won two of three sets, 7-5, 6-2, 
2-6. 
</P>
<P>
 Corona del Mar will play Thursday at Dana Hills. MELANIE NEFF 
</P>
</TEXT>
