<P>
 In other Division I matches: 
</P>
<P>
 Dana Hills 11, Camarillo 7 -- Michele Johnson and Katie Tierney swept at 
doubles, 6-2, 6-3, 7-5, for host Dana Hills (17-3). 
</P>
<P>
 Palos Verdes Peninsula 10, Newport Harbor 8 -- Despite some good play from 
Newport Harbor's No. 1 singles player Sarah Hawkins, who won two of her three 
sets, and the No. 2 doubles team of Vanessa Godbey and Emily Barker, who swept, 
7-5, 6-3, 6-4, the Sailors could not stop top-ranked Palos Verdes Peninsula 
(22-0).Newport Harbor finished 10-7. 
</P>
<P>
 Woodbridge 10, Santa Barbara 8 -- Natalie Exon, Alyssa Artunian and Rachel 
Gunther each won two of three singles sets for visiting Woodbridge (18-4). 
Woodbridge will play top-seeded Palos Verdes Peninsula.  
</P>
<P>
 In Division II matches: 
</P>
<P>
 El Dorado 11, Alhambra 7 -- Linda Surapruik swept her singles sets, 6-3, 6-0, 
6-1, and Brittany McMillian and Susan Surapruik swept their doubles sets, 6-2, 
6-0, 6-0, for El Dorado (20-5). El Dorado will play Hemet on Thursday at a site 
to be determined. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach 14, Edison 4 -- Sarah Cohen and Vanessa Zajfen swept in doubles, 
6-3, 6-0, 6-4, for host Laguna Beach (21-1). Edison finishes 14-7. The 
top-seeded Artists play the Calabasas-Diamond Bar winner in Thursday's 
semifinals. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Alamitos 12, Los Angeles Marlborough 6 -- Alison Miller and Michelle 
Schneider swept their doubles sets, 7-6, 6-4, 6-1, and Laura Springoski and 
Sonja Ralli swept their sets, 6-3, 7-5, 6-4, for Los Alamitos (20-1). 
</P>
<P>
 University 10, Beverly Hills 8 -- The doubles teams of Gillian Kane and 
Malavika Dore and Katy Clark and Jennifer Krupoff each swept their sets for 
visiting University (13-5). 
</P>
