<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL '94-'95: EMPIRE LEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Loara 03,17,09,08 1993-94 RECORDS OVERALL LEAGUE 12-14 2-8 02,11,18 COACH 
RECORD AT SCHOOL Ed Prange 36-63 RETURNING STARTERS: None 04,16,05,06,04 TOP 
RETURNERS YR. HGT. P Dan Hoggatt Sr. 6-2 F Marcus McBride Jr. 5-10 G Antonio 
Moss Sr. 6-2 F 04,18,05,06,04 TOP NEWCOMERS YR. HGT. P Jon Goulding Jr. 6-3 C 
Carlos Guzman Jr. 5-10 G Bryan Hollenbeck Sr. 6-0 F Mark Moses Jr. 5-11 G Obaid 
Popal So. 6-1 G Neil Thomas So. 5-10 G OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 The Saxons are young and inexperienced, so they might take some lumps this 
season. "We're emphasizing getting better with every practice and every game," 
Prange said. Hoggatt is the most experienced player, and he only started two or 
three games last season, Prange said. "He's the only one with a whole season of 
varsity experience. Dan and Tony (Moss) need to score and rebound for us." 
McBride, who starts at running back for the football team, should be the point 
guard. Popal, up from the junior varsity, and Thomas, the freshman MVP, are two 
of the team's best shooters. Both will see significant action. Moses, JV MVP, 
will also see time at off-guard. Goulding and Hollenbeck are key reserves on 
the front line. "This team has the best work ethic of any I've had," Prange 
said. "That's what makes me excited because I think they can improve." SCHEDULE 
</P>
<P>
 November 28-30 at National Sports Grill tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 December 1-3 at National Sports Grill tournament; 8-10 at Cerritos Valley 
Christian tournament; 14 vs. Magnolia; 16 vs. Orange Lutheran; 22 at Anaheim; 
26-30 at Canyon tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 January 4 at Western; 11 vs. Century; 13 at Katella; 18 vs. Kennedy; 20 vs. 
Cypress; 25 at El Dorado; 27 vs. Katella. 
</P>
<P>
 February 1 at Century; 3 at Cypress; 8 at Kennedy; 10 vs. El Dorado. 
</P>
<P>
 TimesLine: (714) 808-8463. School code: *4380 
</P>
