<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: CYPRESS; COUNCIL HONORS CITY'S FAMILY OF THE YEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL BILLITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Brad and Robin Smith and their three children are the city's Family of the 
Year. 
</P>
<P>
 Mayor Richard Partin presented the Smiths with a plaque after the City Council 
announced that they had won the annual Family of the Year competition. 
</P>
<P>
 Each year, families are nominated for the honor, and a volunteer committee 
picks the winner. 
</P>
<P>
 Partin, in reading the city's proclamation, said that the Smiths "have been 
found to be fine examples of a loving family and active in their church." 
</P>
<P>
 Partin added: "There is a great deal of love and devotion in the Smiths' home, 
and the Smiths are a close family who enjoy camping trips and strive to include 
both sets of grandparents in all family outings and activities." 
</P>
<P>
 Brad Smith, an educational consultant, grew up in the city and attended 
Cypress High School and Cypress College. His wife, Robin, a homemaker, grew up 
in Fountain Valley. The couple have lived in the city for the past four years 
and have two daughters, Amber, 9, and Autumn, 6, and a son, Landon, 21 months 
old. 
</P>
<P>
 Robin Smith said she did not know the family had been nominated until she was 
told they had won the annual honor. "I was surprised but thrilled," she said. 
</P>
<P>
 She thinks spending time together is essential to maintaining a strong family. 
</P>
<P>
 "We plan family vacations and spend quality time together," she said. "At 
least once or twice a week we do things totally involved as a family. We also 
are involved with our girls' school and things like that." BILL BILLITER 
</P>
</TEXT>
