<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIRE AT SUBSTATION KNOCKS OUT POWER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A fire in a Southern California Edison substation near the Huntington Beach 
Pier cut off power to about 15,000 customers in the northern section of the 
city as well as western Santa Ana, an Edison spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Power was restored to all customers within 45 minutes, according to Ken Perry, 
a company spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
 The fire started just after 8 p.m., when a circuit breaker in the unoccupied 
substation failed, Perry said. Company officials went to the station and 
extinguished the blaze, which caused minor damage. 
</P>
