STORE CLERK SHOOTS ARMED ROBBER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEANNETTE REGALADO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A convenience store clerk shot an armed robber and scared off his accomplice 
Tuesday night, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Two men, one armed with a semiautomatic pistol, came into the Arrowhead Market 
in the 600 block of West Avenue J about 6:45 p.m. and ordered store clerk 
Manhal Samaan, 30, to give them all of the store's money, Deputy Jeff Cannon of 
the Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department said. 
</P>
<P>
 Samaan reached under the counter for his own handgun and shot one robber, 
Cannon said. Both robbers then fled the store. 
</P>
<P>
 A short time later, Christian George, 18, of Lancaster, came to Antelope 
Valley Hospital Medical Center with a bullet wound in his chest, Cannon said. 
Deputies arrested George on suspicion of attempted robbery. He was listed in 
critical condition at the hospital. The investigation is continuing, Cannon 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The robber's gun was found at the store, Cannon said. The second robber was 
still at large, Cannon said. 
</P>
<P>
 Samaan was not injured. JEANNETTE REGALADO 
</P>
