 Orange County, once a bedroom annex of Los Angeles, has grown into a major 
export-driven economy, as shown in estimates of its gross economic output, and 
values of its major exports: 
</P>
<P>
 ECONOMIC OUTPUT, in billions of 1984 dollars: $69.0 (95 estimate) 
</P>
