</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Transamerica Life Moving 230 Jobs to North Carolina: Transamerica Life Cos., 
citing tax disadvantages in California, said it will change the domicile of its 
seven companies -- Transamerica Life Insurance & Annuity Co.-- to North 
Carolina. As a result, two of the company's business units, with 230 employees, 
will be relocated by the end of 1996, Los Angeles-based Transamerica Life said. 
Because California taxes certain annuity and pension products that other states 
do not, the company incurs "retaliatory" taxes that can be avoided by changing 
its domicile to North Carolina, Transamerica Life said. About 1,700 
Transamerica Life employees will remain in Los Angeles. 
