<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSMAKERS: IRVINE'S INVITRO INTERNATIONAL PICKS PRESIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 W. Richard Ulmer has joined InVitro International, an Irvine developer of 
product safety tests, as president and chief executive. Ulmer was previously 
president of Wilshire Transdermal Products Limited, a subsidiary of Wilshire 
Technologies. He succeeds William J. Fisher, who resigned from the posts in 
August. Before that, Ulmer spent 25 years at Allergan Inc. Among his positions 
were president of Allergan Pharmaceuticals, president of Allergan Medical 
Optics and president of Herbert Laboratories (Allergan Herbert), a skin-care 
division. 
</P>
<P>
 * Thomas E. Pistilli has been appointed president, chief executive and chief 
financial officer of Micro General Corp., a Santa Ana manufacturer of shipping 
and mailing equipment. He succeeds George D. O'Leary, who is resigning to 
pursue other interests, the company said. Pistilli is the former president and 
chief executive of International Mailing Systems Inc. in Shelton, Conn., and 
was a business consultant to Micro General during the past two years. 
</P>
<P>
 * Bruce M. Fried has been appointed vice president for federal affairs at FHP 
International Corp., a Fountain Valley health-care service company. Fried was 
previously executive vice president of Wexler Group, a federal and state 
government relations firm in Washington. During 1992, he was chief coordinator 
of the Clinton-Gore Campaign Health Care Advisory Group and was a member of the 
Presidential Transition Health Care Policy Team. He succeeds Janet Newport, who 
is relocating to the Fountain Valley headquarters as vice president for 
government programs. She will oversee federal regulatory policy and government 
contracting compliance.  
</P>
<P>
 * Doug Semer has been promoted to automotive technical service director for 
American Suzuki Motor Corp. in Brea. He had been national service manager since 
1992. In his new position, Semer will oversee all service branches for the 
automotive division and will be responsible for 17 district service managers. 
</P>
<P>
 * Marci Sawyer has joined Deloitte & Touche in Costa Mesa as manager of 
multi-state tax consulting. She was previously director of tax services for 
Foodmaker Inc., owner of the Jack in the Box and Chi-Chi's restaurant chains. 
Before that, Sawyer was corporate tax manager for First Capital Life Insurance 
Co. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jennifer L. Branin has been appointed vice president for Fieldman, Rolapp & 
Associates, an Irvine financial adviser to local governments. She had been with 
the company from 1986 to early 1991 before joining an East Coast securities 
firm as a financial consultant. 
</P>
<P>
 * Bill Fallon has been appointed director of leasing for Irvine Retail 
Properties Co., a division of Irvine Co. He will oversee leasing activities at 
the company's 18 community and neighborhood shopping centers in Irvine and 
Newport Beach. Before joining Irvine Co., Fallon was leasing manager at Hollis 
& Associates and before that was sales manager for six years with Parker 
Commercial Brokerage Co. in Costa Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
 * Michael Spiekerman has been named vice president of marketing and operations 
for Mitsubishi Electronics America Inc.'s Consumer Electronics Group in 
Cypress. Spiekerman joined the company earlier this year as assistant to the 
president. Before that, he practiced law in Orange County, and he was with TRW 
Inc. for 18 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
